    <div style="background: linear-gradient(100deg, rgba(0,0,0,0.8) 0%, rgba(0,0,0,0.8) 100%), url('https://www.real-estate.ca/uploads/agent-1/calgary/e-calgary/southview/amenities/southview-wm-1.webp'); background-size: cover; min-height: 300px; background-position: center; display: flex; align-items: center; padding: 10%; border-radius: 3px; box-shadow: rgba(50, 50, 93, 0.25) 0px 13px 27px -5px, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3) 0px 8px 16px -8px; margin-bottom: 30px;">
        <h2 style="color: #f9f9f9; margin-bottom: 0; padding-bottom: 0; font-size: 35px; line-height: 1.2; text-shadow: 0px 0px 2px #FFFFFF;">
            Cliff Bungalow Real Estate &mdash; <span style="text-transform: initial;"> a warm, family-friendly neighbourhood that is characterized by its enviable location and abundance of green spaces.</span>
        </h2>
    </div>
    <div class="grid_12">
        <div class="x6">
            <p>Cliff Bungalow is a South West inner city Calgary neighbourhood that is located along 5 Street SW. The neighbourhood is bordered by Elbow River on the South, Fourth Street on the East and Uptown 17th Avenue on the North. The neighbourhood is over a century old and was built in the 1870s on land that was owned by the Canadian Pacific Railway. As one of Calgary's oldest neighbourhoods, the area still has many remnants of its past. The neighbourhood offers historical tours for residents that are interested in learning about the past. Some of the older buildings that still remain in the area include Western Canada High School, 5A Street Boulevards, Holy Angels School, College Apartments and Cliff Bungalow School. Some other historical buildings in the area that are covered on the neighbourhood tour include Somerville Duplex, Giffin Residence, Laurence Apartments and Millican Residence.</p>
            <p>The small and family-friendly neighbourhood offers residents a variety of green spaces and stunning properties located within minutes of downtown Calgary. The community is located alongside the picturesque Elbow River and offers numerous walkways and pathways. Lindsay Park, a beautiful riverside park, is located next to the Elbow river and offers Cliff Bungalow residents plenty of space for walks, picnics and dedicated off-leash dog walking. For residents looking for more hard-core fitness options, the MNP Community & Sport Centre is located within Lindsay Park. The year-round facility offers a variety of fitness options including swimming pools, running tracks, gyms and more.</p>
            <p>Cliff Bungalow is located close to a variety of shopping and entertainment options. 17th Avenue and 4th Street located nearby are home to trendy shops and popular restaurants such as Earl's Tin Palace and Mercato Restaurant. The Calgary Exhibition and Stampede Grounds are located a few blocks away from Cliff Bungalow while residents can visit 4 St SW for any dining and nightlife needs. For residents looking for a quick coffee break, there are several coffee shops located minutes away. These include Du Centre, Purple Perk, Jugo Juice, Western Coffee Shop and Starbucks. Neighbourhood restaurants don't disappoint either and offer a variety of cuisines ranging from Mediterranean delicacies to sushi. Several popular establishments are Anejo Restaurant, Towa Sushi, Aida's Mediterranean and Original Joe's Restaurant & Bar.</p>

