    <div>
        <p>Cliff Bungalow also has an active community association which it shares with the neighbouring <a href="/mission.php">Mission</a> neighbourhood. The community offers a variety of year-round programs for residents and hosts events including Jazz Nights, Board Game Evenings and more. The annual Lilac Festival that is thrown by the community is especially popular. The community is also elder-friendly with the Riverwalk Retirement Residence located within the neighbourhood.</p>
        <p>The neighbourhood is home to several schools to suit all ages and backgrounds. There are Catholic schools, public schools, private schools and even several daycare centres located close by. Homes are characterized by large mature trees, classic white picket fences and plenty of vintage charm. The average price of Cliff Bungalow homes ranges widely with $1.7 million at the high point while condos have an average sale price of $500,000. The neighbourhood is extremely walkable with many conveniences located close by.</p>
        <p>Cliff Bungalow is located next to the communities of <a href="/mission.php">Mission</a>, <a href="/lower-mount-royal.php">Lower Mount Royal</a> and <a href="/beltline.php">Beltline</a> which adds more entertainment options for the residents. Some of the amenities and restaurants located within Cliff Bungalow and around include Safeway, Una Pizza, Jinya, Trolley 5 Brewpub, Yann Haute Patisserie, The Ship & Anchor, Good Life Fitness, Canadian Tire and more. The closest churches to the neighbourhood are Sainte-Famille Church, Calgary Full Gospel Church, Christ Church Anglican Calgary and Grace Presbyterian Church. There are also several must-visit attractions located close by, including Calgary Tower, Glenbow Museum, Calgary Stampede Grounds, Saddledome, Pinbar and Vertigo Theatre.</p>
